{"lemma":"دِيباجٌ","slug":"دِيباجٌ","root":"د.ب.ج","root_slug":"د-ب-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ب-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11980"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"silk brocade","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"وَنَهَانَا عَنْ سَبْعٍ، عَنْ خَاتَمِ الذَّهَبِ ـ أَوْ قَالَ حَلْقَةِ الذَّهَبِ ـ وَعَنْ لُبْسِ الْحَرِيرِ، وَٱلدِّيبَاجِ، وَٱلسُّنْدُسِ، وَٱلْمَيَاثِرِ.","english":"And he forbade us seven things: to wear golden signets – or golden rings –, to wear silk, silk brocade, fine silk or silk saddle-pillows."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spruce decoration, brilliant fashion, beauty","tags":["collective","figuratively"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Middle Persian [script needed] (dypʾk' /⁠dēbāg⁠/, “brocade”). See Classical Persian دیبا (dēbā) for more. Doublet of دَوَاج (dawāj, “bed-quilt”)."},"ipa":["/diː.baːd͡ʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11980","headword_ar":"دِيبَاجٌ","root":"dbj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayobaAjN","text_ar":"دَيْبَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th,) or both, (IAar, A'Obeyd,) the latter having been sometimes heard, (IAar,) or the latter is post-classical, (A'Obeyd,) or wrong, (AZ,) a word of well-known meaning, (K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Silk brocade;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain kind of cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment, made of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iboriysam","text_ar":"اـِبْرِيسَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raw silk"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment, of which the warp and woof are both of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abrysm","text_ar":"ابريسم"},{"kind":"text","text":": and particularly a name for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which is variegated, decorated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"embellished:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of woven stuff, variegated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diversified, with colours:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lb, TA:) [accord. to Golius, as on the authority of the S and K, in neither of which is the word explained at all, “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vestis serica:"},{"kind":"text","text":"imprimis"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"picta,"},{"kind":"text","text":"pec."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Attalica, auro intexta:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabaja","text_ar":"دَبَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ks:) or it is a Pers. word, (Kr, S, A,) arabicized; (Kr, S, A, Msb, K;) so some say, and from it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabaja","text_ar":"دَبَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is derived; (Msb;) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diybaAYo","text_ar":"دِيبَاىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diybaA","text_ar":"دِيبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Kr;) [or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diybaAho","text_ar":"دِيبَاهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for the change of the final"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":"in arabicized words from the Pers. is very common;] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diywo baAfo","text_ar":"دِيوْ بَافْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. “ the weaving of the deevs, or jinn, or genii: ” (Shifá el-Ghaleel:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayaAbiyju","text_ar":"دَيَابِيجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabaAbiyju","text_ar":"دَبَابِيجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) the latter being from the supposed original form of the sing., i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dib~aAjN","text_ar":"دِبَّاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danaAniyru","text_ar":"دَنَانِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diynaArN","text_ar":"دِينَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is supposed to be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"din~aArN","text_ar":"دِنَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in like manner is formed the dim. [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duyayobiyjN","text_ar":"دُيَيْبِيجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dubayobiyjN","text_ar":"دُبَيْبِيجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diybaAju AlquroA=ni","text_ar":"دِيبَاجُ القُرْا=نِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a title given by Ibn-Mes'ood to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The chapters of the Kur-án called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHawaAmiymu","text_ar":"الحَوَامِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fortieth and six following chapters;"},{"kind":"text","text":"each of which begins with the letters"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H`m=","text_ar":"حٰم="},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also the paragraph next following, in two places.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young she-camel; one in the prime of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Th","IAar","AZ","K","TA","Mgh","Msb","Lb","Ks","Kr","S","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}